value.0: These thin leather gloves are several centuries old, but due to their lasting enchantments, they still provide the wearer with greatly improved physical strength.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
This well made halberd was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The halberd is the most common polearm, and could be called a cross between a spear and an axe.  Such weapons are often mass-produced for militia, and serve well when defending against marauders.
This well made short sword was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
One of the first types of sword to come into existence, the short sword is a double-edged weapon about two feet long.  it is an economical weapon, and a favorite of archers and rogues.

This well made chainmail is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments, it still provides a measure of protection to its wearer as first intended.
Piecemeal or complete armors of this type are considered equivalent to scale mail.
These well worn boots have been broken in and can be moved about in easily while working or fighting.
Boots come in a variety of forms and functions, but they do not add the protection given b y basic armor unless infused with magic.

This well made hammer is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments it is as ready for battle as ever.
Originally adapted from the tools of laborers and craftsmen, the warhammer is a far-heavier variant of the sledge and is no longer suitable for anything but combat.
This well made small shield is several centuries old, but due to its lasting enchantments, it appears as ready for battle as ever.
When used properly, a small shield can grant lightweight protection with very little encumbrance to the wielder.

Dhenna was a tanned woman of shorter stature who insists that she saw the god Valkur when she was just a child. Most people simply laugh her off, but some rare few say she might be a Wavetamer.
These thin leather gloves are several centuries old, but due to their lasting enchantments, they still provide archers with alacrity on the battlefield as first intended.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
This device appears to be a silver medallion in the shape of a beetle.  It provides the wearer with several highly sought-after benefits, which become known to one who holds the device for one round.
Amulets are necklaces with some form of large decoration of symbol.  Most are ornamental, but some are potent magic items.
This girdle was made for the benefit of armored, mounted riders.
This well made longsword was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The longsword is the weapon most commonly associated with knights and their ilk.  There are many variations in the blade, but all are approximately 35 to 47 inches in length.

Bromwood was quick on his feet and yet very mindful of his work. He seemed to enjoy a living on what appeared to be extremely hard labor. Loading and unloading caravans weren't things he could do forever, though.

Tyne yn Zendeth el Fahd was a well-known caravan master that held contracts with several pashas who profited from commerce on the Tethir Road and the Trade Way. He was also one of the many businessmen that enabled Faruk Barakat to achieve his successes at bringing his products from far and wide.

This ancient looking stone is covered in lichen and marks from travelers long since past and dead. Still, engraved much deeper than anyone can defile is the name of the road the person is traveling upon...
